column24: Call List Agent, Lock Box, Appointment Required
column25: A truly unique home. It is the owner’s dream come true. The design is based on a book “Your Engineered House” written by a Groton resident, Rex Roberts. It is designed for energy efficiency. The tall south facing windows allow for passive solar gain. The large overhang on the front shades the windows in Summer and allows the sun rays in during the Winter months. The inverted trusses set on posts allow for an open and flexible floor plan. They also create the vaulted ceiling that extends the entire length of the home. The entire house is constructed of native pine. Every piece of lumber was felled by the owner and the trees were milled at a friend’s lumber mill. After the lumber dried it was sent off to be planed. Other than the sliding glass doors and steel beams all construction components were created on site. This unique home is sited on an open lot on the East side of town with beautiful easterly views. This is truly a custom built home created from a dream.
